==English==
===Etymology===
:'''1830''' ''And they did also carry with them '''deseret''', which, by interpretation, is a honey bee; and thus they did carry with them swarms of bees, and all manner of that which was upon the face of the land, seeds of every kind.'' — Joseph Smith, ''Book of Mormon'', Ether 2:3.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# Mormon name for Utah.
#:'''1872''' ''In 1849 the Mormons organized a "free and independent" government and erected the "State of '''Deseret'''," with Brigham Young as its head. But the very next year Congress deliberately snubbed it and created the "Territory of Utah" out of the same accumulation of mountains, sage-brush, alkali and general desolation, -- but made Brigham Governor of it.'' — Mark Twain, ''Roughing It'', [http://etext.virginia.edu/etcbin/ot2www-pubeng?specfile=/texts/english/modeng/publicsearch/modengpub.o2w&act=surround&offset=154525237&tag=EAF504&query=Deseret&id=eaf504 Appendix A]